race.comment: YES MAXI (11) found the line strongly for second over this track and trip last time. Backs up quickly and is drawn to settle much closer. Will take plenty of beating. ETCHED IN BLUE (9) battled away soundly into fourth when resuming at Tatura three weeks ago. Sure to have tightened from that and gets a key booking in McDougall. Bold showing anticipated. NORTHERN EXPOSURE (7) has the fitness edge and should be ready to peak. Likely to cross from the draw and run them along. HELLS SPIRIT (10) strips fitter fourth-up after showing good tactical speed last time before fading late. Drops back in trip on the short turnaround and is worth thought. MIDNIGHT IN MINORI (12) finds it tough to break through but has peaks that measure up. Not to be dismissed completely.
